Anup Ghoshal, mostly known for the 'Tujhse Naraz Nahi Zindagi' number from the 1983 film 'Masoom', passed away at the age of 77. He had worked with renowned directors such as Satyajit Ray.

Matthew Perry died from an accidental ketamine overdose, according to the medical examiner's office. The 'Friends' star had struggled with addiction for years and had been clean for 19 months before his death. Ketamine is a recreational drug known for its numbing & hallucinogenic effects, but it is also used as an anesthetic and in mental health treatments.

A documentary 'To Kill A Tiger', based on the Jharkhand gangrape case has been shortlisted.

The biographical drama '12th Fail,' directed by Vidhu Vinod Chopra & starring Vikrant Massey, is set to release on OTT platform Disney+ Hotstar on Dec 29. The movie tells the inspiring true story of IPS officer Manoj Kumar Sharma and highlights the complexities of the education system in India. The film was well-received by critics and audiences in theaters.

The makers of the upcoming movie 'Main Atal Hoon' have released the first song "Desh Pehle" as a tribute to late former PM Vajpayee on the occassion of his 99th Birth Anniversary. Mbongeni Ngema, writer of the acclaimed musical 'Sarafina' about student riots in apartheid Soweto, was killed in a car crash. Ngema was a writer, lyricist, composer, director, choreographer, and theatre producer.
